  "prompt": "I lost my prescription slip for norco 10-325 before having filled it what can I do?",
  "response": "Losing a prescription before filling it can be frustrating, but here's what you should do:\n\n1.  **Contact the Prescribing Doctor Immediately:** This is the most important step. Explain the situation to the doctor's office (or the covering physician if your doctor is unavailable). They are the only ones who can authorize a new prescription.\n    *   They will likely want to verify your identity and confirm the original prescription details.\n    *   They might ask you questions about how the prescription was lost to prevent potential misuse.\n    *   Depending on office policy and regulations, they may be able to call the prescription into the pharmacy directly, or provide you with a new written prescription.\n\n2.  **Contact Your Pharmacy (If Applicable):** If you usually use a specific pharmacy, it's a good idea to call them as well.\n    *   They may have a record of the prescription being sent to them electronically (if that's how your doctor usually sends prescriptions).\n    *   Even if they don't have a record, they can be ready to receive the new prescription from your doctor.\n\n3.  **Be Prepared to Provide Information:** When you contact the doctor and pharmacy, be ready to provide:\n    *   Your full name and date of birth\n    *   The name of the medication (Norco 10-325)\n    *   The doctor who prescribed it\n    *   The approximate date the prescription was written\n    *   The pharmacy you intended to use (if you had one in mind)\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Controlled Substance:** Norco (hydrocodone/acetaminophen) is a controlled substance.  Prescribing rules are strict due to the potential for misuse and addiction.  Your doctor might be hesitant to issue a new prescription immediately and may want to discuss the situation further.\n*   **Honesty is Crucial:** Be completely honest with your doctor about how the prescription was lost.\n*   **Do not attempt to get a prescription from multiple doctors:** This is illegal and can have serious consequences.\n\nI hope this helps!\n",
